meanings: (연락·연줄 등이) be in touch (with), have connections[contact(s)] (with)

vlive.korean: 안 닿게 해볼게요 열심히. I'll try my best to not touch your skin. 듣기 View video HOONION : [Challenge] 화알못친구에게 안젤리나졸리 메이크업을 받아본다면? makeup challenge
vlive.english: I'll try my best to not touch your skin.

vlive.korean: 최대한 안 닿게 먹어야 돼요. Try to eat it without touching your lips. 듣기 View video MAMAMOO : 래퍼라인 벌칙 수행 '매운돈까스' 시식!! 두둥!!
vlive.english: Try to eat it without touching your lips.

vlive.korean: 몰라. - 얘가 피부에 닿게. I don't know. - This has to touch the skin. 듣기 View video HOONION : [Challenge] 화알못친구에게 안젤리나졸리 메이크업을 받아본다면? makeup challenge
vlive.english: I don't know. - This has to touch the skin.

vlive.korean: 손목에 닿게, 둥글둥글하게. I made it like an arch to fit it on my wrist. 듣기 View video C-JeS : '쇼핑왕 루이' 임세미와 함께 팔찌 만들러 가요!
vlive.english: I made it like an arch to fit it on my wrist.

vlive.korean: 허리가 땅에 닿게 하는 게 중요해요. make sure you back is touching the ground. 듣기 View video GAVYNJ : 추석때 돼지된 사람 드루와~~~~
vlive.english: make sure you back is touching the ground.

examples.korean: The car only just cleared the gatepost. 발음듣기 승용차는 간신히 대문 기둥에 안 닿게 지나갔다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: The car only just cleared the gatepost. 발음

examples.korean: He rolled onto his back. 발음듣기 그는 (엎드려 있다가 등이 바닥에 닿게) 바로 돌아누웠다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: He rolled onto his back. 발음

examples.korean: The cat stayed well out of range of the children. 발음듣기 그 고양이는 아이들 손이 전혀 안 닿게 멀찍이 떨어져 있었다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: The cat stayed well out of range of the children. 발음

examples.korean: I hadn’t figured on getting home so late. 발음듣기 나는 그렇게 늦게 집에 닿게 되리라고는 예상하지 못했었다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: I hadn’t figured on getting home so late. 발음

examples.korean: He was out of breath [was panting for breath] from walking up to the top of the hill. 발음듣기 그는 산 정상으로 오르느라 숨이 턱에 닿게 걷고 있었다. 생활 표현 사전
examples.english: He was out of breath [was panting for breath] from walking up to the top of the hill. 발음
